# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase — use EITHER hosted (cloud) OR local CLI (same env names; see below)
# Copy to `.env.local` and adjust. Never commit `.env.local`.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Option A: Hosted Supabase (Dashboard → Project Settings → API) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxxxxx.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# --- Option B: Local Supabase (`npm run db:start` in this repo) ---
# After start, run `npm run db:status` and copy the "anon key" / Project URL.
#
# Minimal (URL defaults to http://127.0.0.1:54321):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_USE_LOCAL=true
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon key from db:status>
#
# Or set URL explicitly (same as API URL from db:status):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon key from db:status>
#
# Quick local setup (after Docker is running):
#   npm run db:start    # first time can take several minutes (image pull)
#   npm run seed        # programme tables + sample rows
#   npm run dev
